Travis Oliphant Keynote PyCon Colombia 2023
description:
🐍🐍 Pycon Colombia 2023 in this edition brings guests from another dimension, This year, we will have the participation of Travis Oliphant, he is the Founder and CEO of OpenTeams and Quansight.  He has spent over 25 years in the open source software scientific computing sector as the creator of NumPy, SciPy, Conda, and Numba and as a Founder of Anaconda (Continuum Analytics), NumFOCUS, and PyData. He has B.S. degrees in Electrical and Computer Engineering and Math, as well as an M.S. in Electrical and Computer Engineering from Brigham Young University and a Ph.D. in Biomedical Engineering from the Mayo Clinic.  He is deeply interested in helping domain experts use Python more effectively to fully utilize hardware by leveraging the power of open source communities.

Deb Nicholson Keynote PyCon Colombia 2023
description:
🐍🐍 Pycon Colombia 2023 in this edition brings guests from another dimension, This year, we will have the participation of Deb Nicholson, she is the Executive Director at the Python Software Foundation, the non-profit steward of the Python programming language. She is a free software policy expert and a passionate community advocate. After years of local organizing on free speech, marriage equality, government transparency and access to the political process, she joined the free software movement in 2006. She has previously served the open source ecosystem through her work at the Open Source Initiative, Software Freedom Conservancy, and the Open Invention Network. She’s won the O’Reilly Open Source Award and the Award for the Advancement of Free Software for her efforts to broaden the free and open source software movement. She is also a founding organizer of the Seattle GNU/Linux Conference, an annual event dedicated to surfacing new voices and welcoming new people to the free software community. She lives with her partner and her lucky black cat in Cambridge, Massachusetts, USA.

LinkedIn: https://www.linkedin.com/in/denicholson 
Twitter: https://twitter.com/baconandcoconut

Catherine Devlin Keynote PyCon Colombia 2023
description:
🐍🐍 Pycon Colombia 2023 in this edition brings guests from another dimension, This year, we will have the participation of Catherine Devlin.
A freak accident in 1999 transformed Catherine Devlin from a chemical engineering graduate student into a database administrator. She got her start with Python at PyCon US 2004, and has been a Python community addict ever since, serving as PyOhio's founding chair in 2008. She works as a data architect for Corning. She lives in the woods near Dayton, OH, USA, with her wife, two cats, and two horses; she usually has sticks in her hair.

title: Gabriela Coleman PyCon Colombia 2023
description:
🐍🐍 Pycon Colombia 2023 in this edition brings guests from another dimension, This year, we will have the participation of Gabriella (Biella) Coleman, she is a full professor in the Department of Anthropology at Harvard University and is a faculty associate at the Berkman Center for Internet and Society. Her scholarship and teaching address questions of science and technology, focusing on the politics, cultures, and ethics of computer hacking. She is the author of two books on computer hackers and the founder and editorof Hack_Curio, a video portal into the cultures of hacking. In 2022,she hosted the BBC4 radio and podcast series, The Hackers. You can learn more about her work here: https://gabriellacoleman.org/

I recorded one video and did not like it (I don't like watching myself on video, I guess) but I will retry this week and send something along!
-Biella

Website: https://gabriellacoleman.org/
